# <type>(<scope>): <short imperative description>
# Example: fix(graphics): resolve alignment issue in scoreboard
# 
# [Optional] Detailed description: Why is this change being made?

# [Optional] Related issues (e.g. Fixes #123)

# --- TYPE GUIDE ---
# feat     : New feature
# fix      : Bug fix
# ui       : Visual changes / CSS / Animations
# docs     : Documentation update (README, etc.)
# refactor : Code change that neither adds a feature nor fixes a bug
# chore    : Maintenance tasks (dependencies, configuration)
# test     : Add or modify tests
# build    : Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
#
# --- COMMON SCOPES GUIDE (Optional) ---
# Omit scope for general Scoreko changes. Use specific scopes when needed:
# (dashboard) : Changes in the dashboard UI
# (graphics)  : Changes in the graphics/overlays
# (extension) : Changes in the extension logic
# (build)     : Changes in scripts, packaging, or native modules
